'''Bead-rim pottery''' refers to the presence of a rounded molding on the lip of a [[jar]], [[bowl]], or [[Dishware|dish]], both to add strength and assist in handling .<ref>{{cite book|last=Darvill|first=Timothy|title=The Concise Oxford Dictionary of Archaeology|year=2003|isbn=0-19-280005-1|pages=42|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iSd8hm5kImwC&pg=PA42&lpg=PA42&dq=bead+rim+pottery&source=bl&ots=cYl1iZPWDY&sig=xJmIOtU5tBFnCWzAy3dk7B2JMwE&hl=en&ei=ViLLTLSuHor_nAe-_Igh&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CCEQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=bead%20rim%20pottery&f=false}}</ref>

