'''Charles Eugène Espidon Goupil''' (14 December 1831 – 24 October 1896) was a [[French Mexican]] [[philanthropist]] and [[collecting|collector]].

In 1889 he bought [[Joseph Marius Alexis Aubin]]'s collection of 384 [[Mesoamerica]]n manuscripts. On 14 May 1864, he married Augustine Élie. After Goupil's death, his wife donated the collection to the [[Bibliothèque Nationale]] in [[Paris]].

Goupil was the great-uncle of artist [[Jean Charlot]].

