{{one source|date=December 2015}} '''Yuri Mihailovich Kilin''' ({{lang-ru|Юрий Михайлович Килин}}, born 1961) is a [[Russia]]n [[historian]] and a [[professor]] of History Studies at the [[Petrozavodsk State University]] in [[Petrozavodsk]]. He has written extensively on Russo-[[Finland|Finnish]] and [[Karelia]]n historical conflicts. Kilin graduated with honours in 1983. He received his [[Candidate of Sciences]] degree in [[Leningrad]] 1991, and [[Doctor of Sciences]] degree in [[Moscow]] 2000. Kilin has written in over 50 publications, including over 25 published aboard.<ref>[http://petrsu.karelia.ru/Chairs/GenHist/kilin.html Petrozavodsk State University: Kilin Yuri Mihailovich] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110824090254/http://petrsu.karelia.ru/Chairs/GenHist/kilin.html |date=August 24, 2011 }} (in Russian)</ref> His name has also [[Romanization of Russian|transliterated]] as '''Juri Kilin'''.
